Preparations are underway for the prestigious Durban July tomorrow. Police are making sure revelers will be safe. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Preparations are underway for the prestigious Durban July. Police are making sure revellers will be safe at Saturday’s horseracing and fashion event. “Police and other security agencies will be on high alert during the Vodacom Durban July this weekend and after-party event at Moses Mabhida People’s Park,” police said in a statement. “Planning between the SAPS, Security Clusters and the event coordinators has been on-going for weeks. “A pro-active approach which resulted in a successful event previously has been adopted for this event. “SAPS officers and personnel will be in and around both areas of events as well as around Durban to tackle the problems which might disrupt the events.”